articles.title: Transient naive reprogramming corrects hiPS cells functionally and epigenetically - Nature.com
articles.description: A new reprogramming strategy used to produce human induced pluripotent stem cells from somatic cells results in epigenetic and functional profiles that are highly similar to those of human embryonic stem cells.
